Package: ssnip
Type: Package
Title: Hypothetical Monopoly Test
Version: 0.1
Author: Peter Foldvari
Maintainer: P. Foldvari <p.foldvari@uva.nl>
Description: 
    SNIP stands for the Small but Significant, Non-transitory Increase in Price method 
    to find a set of goods that constitute a market. It is often used to asses the impact of mergers and acquisitions. 
    ssnip tests for a predefined subset of k goods, sel_ssnip tests for al possible combination of all k goods.
